This paper proposes a new framework for training deep stacked RNNs for sequence tagging tasks. The paper focuses on natural language processing tasks such as POS tagging and CCGbank supertagging, which are typically categorized under cs.CL. The proposed framework involves a gating mechanism and shortcuts, which are common techniques used in deep learning and machine learning, and can be categorized under cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.NE. The paper also mentions experiments with convolutional neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks and can be categorized under cs.CV. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CL, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.CV.
